      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of anticipated clinical loading scenarios; at minimum two load levels or configurations tested.",
      "rationale": "Only a single test configuration (ASTM F1717 standard compression-bending at fixed load rate 5 mm/min, ambient temperature) was employed. No variation in load angle, displacement rate, or environmental condition was explored. Achieved level is Gradation 1; required level is Gradation 2. This shortfall is acknowledged and accepted given the regulatory precedent for single-condition F1717 testing and the conservative nature of the standard protocol."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
